{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/00205696386/1930091501/0104.xml":{"full_text":"8\nBARCLAY FLAYS 1\nU. S. OFFICIALS\nThe Treasury and Postoffice\ndepartments were charged with\nsuppressing facts on unemploy\nment and the business depression\nby Senator Barkley, (D.), of\nKentucky, yesterday.\nBarkley reiterated his declara\ntion that the new tariff bill Is\nendangering foreign trade end\nthe payment of European debts,\ndeclaring the reply of Under Sec\nretary of the Treasury Ogden\nMills was \u201cin some respects amus\ning and in others wholly evasive.\u201d\nBarkley said:\n\u201cIt is perfectly evident that\nthe Treasury Department does\nnot desire to reveal the whele\nfacts with reference to our for\neign trade situation, and I\nmight add that the Postoffice\nDepartment is following the\nsame policy, for it has discon\ntinued for some time the issu\nance of monthly statements\nshowing the postal receipts of\nthe 50 largest cities in the\nUnited States.\n\u201cThis is in line with the policy\nof keeping from the people the\nseal facts concerning unem\nployment and business depres\nsion.\n\u201cIn proof of the recent state\nment which I made concerning\nthe effect of the Hawley-Smoot\ntariff upon our foreign trade,\nthe President of. the United\nStates was yesterday visited by\na delegation of English and\nAmerican business men and\nwarned that the people of En\ngland would not continue to\nbuy grain from the American\nfarmer if unreasonable and in\ndefeasible tariff rates were to\nbe maintained against their\nown country.\u201d\n6-Months-Old Baby\nSwims Into News\nBALTIMORE, Sept. 15.\u2014Mary\nland\u2019s youngest mermaid is six\nmonths old, Phyllis Jane Rappa\nport, daughter of Mr. and Mrs.\nJack Rappaport of Baltimore. The\nmysteries of the eight-beat crawl\nare still unsolved by Baby Jane,\nbut the simpler strokes come\nnatural to her and she gets\nthrough the water at a speed\namazing for one so young.\nAccording to her mother, Jane\n\u2022topped trying to sing in the\nbathtub at the age of two months\nand began to try to swim. By the\ntime she was three months old\nshe could stay afloat without aid.\nJ&j\n'Roofless Anchor Bar\n/f\\ PLATES\nH\\ FIT TIGHT/ M\nLEV STAY tight/\nSls\ntheyUthey\nFEEL Ttl W LOOK\nnatural\nTeeth Extraction* by Expert*\nCrown and Removable Bridgework\nPlaced Without Grinding Tour Teeth\n$5 cQyy ss\nPlate* Repaired WhUe Ton Walt, (1\nDR. LEHMAN\n408 7th St. N. W.\n_ Over Woolworth\u2019* 5 and 10 ___J\nCHAMBERS\nThis neat gray cloth casket,\nplain and dignified, with the\nwhole funeral\u2014\ns loo\nThe lame service a* the higher\npriced funeral*, with no extra charge\nfor chapel. All moelc, If desired, by\noar pipe organ.\nIn Case of Death Call\nTHE GREATER\nI W.W. Chambers Co.\n14th Cor. Chapin St. N.W.\nPhone Columbia 0432\nWhere the Beet Cost* Lets\n1,1\nAt\nYour Command\nMiles of unused mile\nage await Washing\ntonians who are anx-,\nious to know the pleas\nant feeling of being\nable to own a car of\nown the car\nyou want is at ydur\ncommand today. Select\nIt from\u2014\nmmmumfEs\nClassified Ads\n\n{Clarendon to Hear\nTalk on Sewer Work\nCLARENDON. Va\u201e Sept. 16.\nAllen J, Seville, director of the\ngoning of Arlington county, will\nbe the principal speaker at ti\nannual fall membership meeting\nof the Chamber of Commerce, to\nbe held here Thursday night.\nSeville has been asked to talk on\na proposed sewer system for the\ni county.\ncr Wruit\nThe New\nl\ne\nHSBg m ****nWHKm ajHaii J&\nA\n7\nFor\ngr-- j HOUSE HEATING\nMeans to you\n*(The new schedule of rates has been filed with the\nB|HfIBBH|B Public Utilities Commission and is subject to the\nH 19 |||BflH||H Commission\u2019s approval before being put into effect)\nI B \u25a0\u25a0\u25a0l th\u00ab hundreds of Washington home owners who have been enjoying\nI jg Automatic Gas Heating during the past several Winters, the new re-\nduced house heating rate brings a material saving.\nHi For additional hundreds, 